Methods and problematics of a comparative research. Contrasting word derivatives in Russian and Estonian. Grammatical categories of the two languages and their usage.Objectives/eesmärkid:  to find similarities and differences in grammar and lexis of the Estonian and Russian languages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) is aware of the methods of contrastive linguistics and can use them in practice; 2) knows word-formation rules in Russian and Estonian, core features of lexical systems of both languages; 3) knows grammatical system of parts of speech of Russian and Estonian,  knows similarities and differences; 4) can carry out a comparative analysis using Russian and Estonian grammatical terminology; 5) is aware of interference impact on foreign language learning; can classify and prevent the mistakes.
